  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2022-09-22",
    "date": "2022-11-08T15:13:23Z",
    "text": "Preserving the Readiness of our Armed Forces Act of 2022\n\nThis bill provides that a member of the National Guard (or another reserve component) must maintain access to pay and benefits while a request for a religious or health accommodation is pending. Additionally, a member of an active or reserve component of the Armed Forces may not be involuntarily separated from the Armed Forces based solely on COVID-19 vaccination status until specified recruiting goals are achieved."
  },
